<br>
And the list is just simply a statement of clerics saying I am at this level, when so and so is done with the camp, plz inform me so that I can get to the camp.<br>
<br>
Meaning lets say for example that Dreadina has the camp.<br>
After her, I get the camp cause I signed up.<br>
After me, Cleric 3, etc etc etc.<br>
<br>
All it would do was semi formalize the &quot;line&quot; so to speak.<br>
<br>
There is no way to enforce it, it would simply be courtesy.  <br>
<br>
Let me give an example: Lets say that I am second so when Dread is done, she lets me know, I come on over and take the camp.  Lets say that for some odd reason I cannot hold the camp (my kid gets sick or whatever RL thing).. instead of just abandoning the camp, I can ask the next cleric to come in (lets just say that my guild cannot hold it for me for some reason).  That way everyone is happy.<br>
<br>
Or maybe this.. RF pops and I am done .. I call the next cleric but they cannot do it.. so we continue on down the line.  <br>
<br>
I dunno it was an idea we were throwing around so that everyone could get the camp, and no one would have to camp it for a week to get it, and no one would have to be an ass to get it either.  <br>
<br>
/shrug.  Just because its been done one certain way doesnt mean that it works well.  The mob can be taken if another guild is there to hand the item in before the cleric that camped the RF pop has a force there.. thats why when he pops ya want to get there asap.  <br>
<br>
Also I am not sure, but I heard he despawns within an hour.... I might want to check on that.  <br>
<br>
Anyways, it was an idea.. I mean someone(dont recall who) posted that they sure as heck wouldnt wait for some cleric from a no name guild to get their turn.. I mean we all deserve a chance to get the epic piece.. Ill probably have mine before too long.. Dread and I thought itd be kinda cool tho to get a line going, with clerics giving some type of contact info (like an email or a person in guild who can call them in RL) where we can reach the next person in line.  I dunno, that way we dont have any asses trying to steal the camps, and ppl dont have to camp it for three weeks to get it.  <br>
<br>
I mean we would all be pissed if we camped a mob for three days, went LD and then when we came back 10 min later a new cleric was there.  But technically, itd be ok for them to do that, just not courteous.<br>
<br>
Hey, if ya all want to continue to camp it for weeks on end or checking every once in awhile like we are doing to get the camp, then hey, go for it.<br>
<br>
We were just kicking around the idea to try and get it working perhaps a bit better for all clerics.<br>
